      "name": "Hemolysis model adequacy assessment via published literature survey",
      "description": "Published CFD hemolysis studies from peer-reviewed journals were reviewed to assess the adequacy of the power-law hemolysis model. Seventeen prior studies reporting relative hemolysis index predictions for rotary blood pumps were identified and their reported model errors tabulated. The survey concludes that the power-law model achieves acceptable accuracy (mean RH prediction error < 15%) across comparable pump geometries and operating ranges. This literature-based review is considered sufficient to establish model confidence for MRL 2.",
